<br>
The problem with LoH being a CH, especially at lvl 1, is that then you could then have hordes of lvl 1 pallies CHing at high-end encounters.  If near a bindable area (or with cleric epic), you could probably even make a CH cycle out of it by suiciding them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udanaellebladesong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Danaelle Bladesong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/5/02 4:03:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15180.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.cybernetisp.net/jmfranks/coloredcrescent.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions on LOH...</span><hr size=1> Hmmn... guess I'm not twinked/uber enough... I've never yet seen LoH heal me to less than my full hp. Or maybe I hit it early enough that the hp I had left were from buffs etc? Weird. I know if I use it, on say my husband's ranger, it's not a CH because he has more hp than I do. But I didn't realize it would do that at lower levels. Hmmn. Have to watch it now. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=68641" target="_blank">
<img src="http://members.cybernetisp.net/jmfranks/eq/danaesig.jpg" border="0">
</a> 
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueumerin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eumerin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 181<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/5/02 4:09:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15180.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions on LOH...</span><hr size=1> At the lowest levels, its not that big of a deal.  When you start getting your own buffs, or start getting buffed by others, you'll quickly notice that it doesn't quite cover you completely.  My current rule of thumb (I'm at 36 right now, and this rule has been in place for at least the last ten levels) is that it can recover roughly 80% of my hitpoints.<br>
Personal mileage may vary, of course.<br>
 <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=96807 target="web">Eumerin Paxodus</a>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvalyawanderfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valya Wanderfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy Defender</span><br>  Posts: 885<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/5/02 4:14:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15180.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.pacbell.net/skfitz/valface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions on LOH...</span><hr size=1> sounds like the original poster must have a fair amount of HP gear and / or buffs.  <br>
<br>
It works off your unbuffed HP.... this is quite noticeable when I LOH a raid buffed 60 warrior and he gets noticebly less than half his HP back :p <p><font size="+1">	
<a href="http://www.geocities.com/valya_w" target="_blank"><b><u>Valya Wanderfoot </u></b></a>, </font><br>60 Crusader<br>
