everything. They're like plotting the revolution, man. I wouldn't mess with them." --Michael Moore, 2002</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalidin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balidin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 267<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/5/02 4:19:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15180.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions on LOH...</span><hr size=1> If I'm naked, actually, LH is effectively a CH for me (level 48 LH did 1700, never had to LH yet in 49), since my base HP is around 1400. I have just barely over 1700 HP now with just gear and no buffs; if I LH last level at 1 HP, I would come very very close to full. However, with my buffs (full buffs including Pinzarn), I'm at around 2310HP, so LH isn't a CH for me any more.<br>
<br>
Point: <br>
*muttering in background. one voice rises to audible level:*<br>
&quot;Uhh guys, did we even have a point?&quot;<br>
<br>
Well I guess the point is that LH is only a CHeal on a CR after around level 20 or 30. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><font><font size=3><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45984>Balidin</a>,</font> The Evilbasher</b><BR><font color=red><i>Paladin of the 4900th LFG</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthelionfist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Lionfist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/5/02 4:44:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15180.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~carriedingus/profile.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions on LOH...</span><hr size=1> Aye, I do have a pretty obscene amount of HP twinkage on my Pally. I am building him as a total HP/STA machine.<br>
<br>
I guess that is why I noticed it.<br>
<br>
It's not even 1/2 my 630 self buffed HP at level 10.<br>
<br>
I realize that I am twinked, I don't deny it or try to make a big deal out of it either way, I just wanted to make sure that I was right about my assumption that the LoH was based on my naked HP, and it appears to be so, as the numbers LoH's doing coincide with my naked HP, which is way less than gear. I have to tactically behave like I get a 1/2 heal and not a CH, is all.<br>
<br>
As I level, the gap of HP from gear vs &quot;natural&quot; HP will close a lot, looks like.<br>
<br>
Thanks for responses.<br>
<br>
BTW, got a great feeling today, landed a LoH on a unconsious, bleeding to death stranger. Very good feeling to hit LoH on what looks like a corpse, to see it come back to life.<br>
<br>
=) <p><center><img src = "http://home.earthlink.net/~carriedingus/lionfist.gif"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugraalthedorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Graal the Dorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 213<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/5/02 4:55:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15180.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions on LOH...</span><hr size=1> >>It works off your unbuffed HP.... this is quite noticeable when I LOH a raid buffed 60 warrior and he gets noticebly less than half his HP back :p <<<br>
<br>
LoH has nothing to do with your hp at all, it is based on a formula that scales with level. It used to be 30 * level, but was given a boost a long time ago, probably about 6 months after Kunark came out.<br>
<br>
I wouldn't be surprised if it was 35 * level now. <p><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14686"> Graal MacBladefury</A><BR>
